block content

  .ui.text.container.addBottomMargin
    br   
    p The concept and consequences of identity theft (submodule 1)          
    p Learn 3/4
    .ui.raised.segment
      h3 Definition
      p <u>Identity theft</u> is when your personal identifiable information (PII) is stolen and used against you.

      p <u>Personal Identifiable Information (PII)</u> is information uniquely associated with you, which can be directly or indirectly used to identify you.

      h4 Here are some specific examples of PII:
      ul
        li Name: full name, maiden name, mother’s maiden name, or alias
        li Personal identification numbers: social security number (SSN), passport number, driver’s license number, taxpayer identification number, patient identification number, financial account number, or credit card number
        li Personal address information: street address, or email address
        li Personal telephone numbers

